"script": "Could you grow a real diamond inside a metal box? Well, scientists do it every single day. First, a tiny sliver of real diamond is placed in a sealed chamber filled with carbon gas. Then the chamber is blasted with microwave energy until the gas glows like a purple star. And this superheats the carbon until atoms rain down onto the seed, one layer at a time. Next, over several weeks, the crystal grows thicker, identical to one ripped from deep underground. Finally, it's cut and polished, and not even a jeweler can tell it was born in a machine.",
